Package imagingbook.common.geometry.circle

Class AlgebraicCircle

  • java.lang.Object
    • imagingbook.common.geometry.circle.AlgebraicCircle
  • public class AlgebraicCircle
extends Object
    Represents an algebraic circle with four parameters A, B, C, D in the form A * (x^2 + y^2) + B * x + C * y + D = 0. Parameters are normalized such that B^2 + C^2 - 4 * A * D = 1 and A ≥ 0 Circle instances are immutable.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AlgebraicCircle

        public AlgebraicCircle​(double A,
                       double B,
                       double C,
                       double D)
        Constructor. Creates a AlgebraicCircle instance whose parameters A, B, C, D are normalized such that B^2 + C^2 - 4 * A * D = 1 and A ≥ 0. Throws an exception if d = B^2 + C^2 - 4 * A * D (the discriminant) is negative.
        Parameters:
        A - circle parameter A
        B - circle parameter B
        C - circle parameter C
        D - circle parameter D
